==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chastisement
<hw>Chas"tise*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Chastise</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of chastising; pain inflicted for
punishment and correction; discipline; punishment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shall I so much dishonor my fair stars,⟦br⟧
On equal terms to give him <qex>chastesement</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have borne <qex>chastisement</qex>; I will not offend any
more.</q> <rj><qau>Job xxxiv. 31.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chastiser</ent>⟦br⟧
